# MathScript Oracle Cloud Deployment Rules

## VM Setup (one-time)
```bash
# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install Python + Node
sudo apt install -y python3.11 python3.11-venv python3-pip nodejs npm git

# Install Java 21 (for Spring Boot migration)
sudo apt install -y openjdk-21-jdk

# Install nginx
sudo apt install -y nginx certbot python3-certbot-nginx

# Open ports in Oracle iptables (Oracle ignores ufw by default!)
sudo iptables -I INPUT 6 -m state --state NEW -p tcp --dport 80 -j ACCEPT
sudo iptables -I INPUT 6 -m state --state NEW -p tcp --dport 443 -j ACCEPT
sudo iptables -I INPUT 6 -m state --state NEW -p tcp --dport 5000 -j ACCEPT
sudo iptables -I INPUT 6 -m state --state NEW -p tcp --dport 8080 -j ACCEPT
sudo netfilter-persistent save
```

## CRITICAL: Oracle Networking
Oracle Cloud has TWO firewall layers:
1. iptables on the VM (managed by `iptables` commands above)
2. OCI Security List/Security Group (managed in OCI Console)
BOTH must allow the port for traffic to reach the app.
If app works on localhost but not from internet → check OCI Security List ingress rules.

## Environment Variables
Create `/home/ubuntu/Mathscript/.env` (never commit this file):
```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mathscript
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=your_key_here
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_...
SESSION_SECRET=generate_a_random_32char_string_here
```

Load in systemd service via `EnvironmentFile=/home/ubuntu/Mathscript/.env`

## Systemd Service (Python FastAPI)
File: `/etc/systemd/system/mathscript.service`
```ini
[Unit]
Description=MathScript FastAPI Backend
After=network.target postgresql.service

[Service]
Type=simple
User=ubuntu
WorkingDirectory=/home/ubuntu/Mathscript
EnvironmentFile=/home/ubuntu/Mathscript/.env
ExecStart=/home/ubuntu/Mathscript/venv/bin/uvicorn backend.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 5000
Restart=always
RestartSec=10

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```
```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable mathscript
sudo systemctl start mathscript
sudo journalctl -u mathscript -f  # watch logs
```

## Nginx Reverse Proxy
File: `/etc/nginx/sites-available/mathscript`
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name themathscript.com www.themathscript.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:5000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
        proxy_read_timeout 90s;
        proxy_connect_timeout 90s;
    }
}
```
```bash
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/mathscript /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

## SSL with Let's Encrypt
```bash
sudo certbot --nginx -d themathscript.com -d www.themathscript.com
sudo certbot renew --dry-run
```

## PostgreSQL on Oracle VM
```bash
sudo apt install -y postgresql postgresql-contrib
sudo -u postgres psql -c "CREATE DATABASE mathscript;"
sudo -u postgres psql -c "CREATE USER mathuser WITH PASSWORD 'strongpassword';"
sudo -u postgres psql -c "GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE mathscript TO mathuser;"
# Then set DATABASE_URL=postgresql://mathuser:strongpassword@localhost:5432/mathscript
```

## Deployment Checklist
- [ ] All env vars set in .env file
- [ ] Frontend built: `cd frontend && npm install && npm run build`
- [ ] Python venv created and dependencies installed: `pip install -r requirements.txt`
- [ ] Database initialized (tables created)
- [ ] Systemd service enabled and running
- [ ] Nginx configured and reloaded
- [ ] OCI Security List has port 80/443 open
- [ ] iptables rules saved
- [ ] SSL certificate installed (production)
- [ ] Stripe webhook endpoint updated to new Oracle URL

## SSH Keep-Alive (already configured in ~/.ssh/config)
```
Host *
    ServerAliveInterval 60
    ServerAliveCountMax 10
    TCPKeepAlive yes
```

## Useful OCI Commands
```bash
# Check what's listening
sudo ss -tlnp | grep -E '5000|8080|80|443'

# Watch app logs live
sudo journalctl -u mathscript -f

# Restart app
sudo systemctl restart mathscript

# Check nginx errors
sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log

# Check Oracle iptables rules
sudo iptables -L INPUT --line-numbers
```
